# QMS Content Generation

When generating or reformatting procedures, policies, or other QMS document content, **output clean, semantic HTML only**. Do not use Markdown. The content will be pasted into a TipTap-based rich text editor.

## Formatting Rules

| Element | Use |
|---------|-----|
| Paragraphs | `<p>...</p>` |
| Headings | `<h1>`, `<h2>`, etc. for section titles |
| Bulleted lists | `<ul>` with `<li>` items |
| Numbered lists | `<ol>` with `<li>` items |
| Bold | `<strong>` |
| Italic | `<em>` |
| Tables | `<table>`, `<thead>`, `<tbody>`, `<tr>`, `<th>`, `<td>` |

## Checklists & Approval Boxes

Use `<ul>` with Unicode checkbox characters:
- `☐` (unchecked)
- `☑` (checked)

Example: `<li>☐ Verified by: __________________</li>`

## Example

```html
<h1>Equipment Calibration Procedure</h1>
<p>This document outlines the process for periodic calibration of measurement equipment.</p>

<h2>1.0 Pre-Calibration Checklist</h2>
<ul>
    <li>☐ Verify equipment is clean and free from damage.</li>
    <li>☐ Confirm calibration standard is within certification date.</li>
</ul>

<h2>2.0 Results Log</h2>
<table>
    <thead>
        <tr><th>Equipment ID</th><th>Parameter</th><th>Status</th></tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
        <tr><td>TEMP-001</td><td>Temperature (°C)</td><td>Pass</td></tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
```

Output a single block of well-formed HTML that can be pasted directly into the editor.
